  "grammar_point": {
    "title": "想 (xiǎng) — want to / would like to",
    "explanation": "想 means 'want to' or 'would like to'. Put it before another verb: 我想吃 = I want to eat, 我想喝 = I want to drink. This is called a verb-verb structure and is very common in Chinese. The question word 什么 (shénme) means 'what'.",
    "examples": [
      { "chinese": "我想喝水", "pinyin": "Wǒ xiǎng hē shuǐ", "english": "I want to drink water" },
      { "chinese": "你想吃什么？", "pinyin": "Nǐ xiǎng chī shénme?", "english": "What do you want to eat?" }
    ]
  },
